    "caption": "The hammer head actually does something really useful.",
    "shortDescription": "The hammerhead shark's wide flat head works like a metal detector sweeping across the seafloor — it's packed with electrical sensors that can find a stingray buried under sand. Their eyes sit at opposite ends of the head, giving them almost 360-degree vision all around their body. Fun fact: Hammerheads can detect the electrical field of a heartbeat from animals hidden under the sand."
